## 11. Alternative Approaches Considered

### 11.1 Pure UXP (No Helper App)

**Approach**: Use WebAssembly version of FFprobe in browser context

**Pros**:
- No external dependencies
- Simpler distribution

**Cons**:
- FFprobe WASM very large (~30MB)
- Performance concerns
- May not support all codecs
- Not officially available

**Verdict**: Not viable currently

### 11.2 CEP Extension Instead of UXP

**Approach**: Use legacy CEP with full Node.js access

**Pros**:
- Direct child_process access
- Well-documented
- Immediate FFprobe execution

**Cons**:
- Deprecated (support until Sept 2026)
- Synchronous API blocks UI
- No future investment from Adobe

**Verdict**: Viable but not future-proof

### 11.3 AppleScript/PowerShell Bridge

**Approach**: Use `shell.openPath()` to run scripts

**Pros**:
- No separate app installation
- Platform-native

**Cons**:
- Cannot capture output
- No progress feedback
- Very fragile

**Verdict**: Not recommended

